The paper deals with the problem of super-resolution for light field cameras, which is a topic that falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The use of graph-based regularization also suggests that the paper may belong to the graphics (cs.GR) or computer graphics (cs.CG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the use of machine learning techniques, which could place it under the machine learning (cs.MM) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories.
